descript.abstract: This data layer represents Parcels for Adams County, Wisconsin in 2012. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, “Adams_Parcels_2012.gdb”.
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
descript.supplinf: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. For additional information, please see original license/data sharing agreement where applicable.

attracc.attraccr: The attribute accuracy is tested by comparison of the source attribute data with the digital data attributes. The Adams County Land Information Office GIS Section checked 100% of the data for attribute accuracy.

dataqual.logic: This data set is topological structured for polygons, arcs, and text for the town areas of Adams County. The geographic data represented by this coverage is stored according to a vector-based data type. With a vector data structure, geographic entities are represented as point, lines, and areas depicted on a 2-dimensional surface. Each point is identified by a single x-y location; lines are identified by a sequence of x-y coordinates; areas are identified by a series of x-y coordinates as defined by line segments that close to form a polygon.
dataqual.complete: The tax parcels represented in this data set are, to the best knowledge of the Adams County Land Information Office, representative of 99% of parcel boundaries and legal descriptions occurring in Adams County. Some features, however, depending on the scale, date, and origin of the source material may be generalized or incomplete and in need of further investigation.

procstep.procdesc: The Adams County Land Information Office maintains the current tax parcel drawings for town areas. Parcels are created and maintained using coordinate geometry methodologies where legal descriptions allow. Where coordinate geometry cannot be used, parcels are entered using the most accurate methods available. The base PLSS coverage is used as a base for all coordinate geometry and other parcel entry and maintenance efforts. In areas where a more detailed GPS is available, that source of information is used.
Changed name of file from Parcel to Adams_Parcel_2012.
